  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. A 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the scale of the crime and the defendant's background. Considering the financial loss and the breach of trust inherent in the position, incarceration is necessary, but a short, rehabilitative term of 6 months is sufficient to uphold the law while allowing for the continued repayment of the remaining debt.",
